{
  "stem": "16930.3",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 227.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He had been-- towards the end of the war, he had joined the-- the British Air Force and was a Sergeant.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he flew a-- a Spitfire.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He learned to-- so he was only like a-- a pilot.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the other pilots for [NON-ENGLISH], the American and British pilots and other South African pilots, who had actually fought-- had fighting experience during the war, used to keep an eye on him, you know that sort of-- a new pilot comes in, the other pilots keep an eye on you, because they don't let you get caught in the middle somewhere by yourself.",
      "word_count": 65
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they kept an eye on him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But one day he did come back and he did have a-- he scored.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he-- he downed a Russian plane.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What was happening, there were several planes going down to the Eilat area somewhere.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were just flying around, but four planes or so.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was from-- I can't think now the airport there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was in the south.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was near [NON-ENGLISH] and they used to fly down there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then four Russian MiGs used to come up, fly above them, chase them away.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they would run, of course, with those-- those little flames, I saw the Russian MiGs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Of course they took off.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the Russians were having a little bit of fun.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then one day, the-- the Yiddish [INAUDIBLE], you know, the-- the Jewish brains, they let those four little guys fly there again in those little planes there.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then MiGs came out after them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But they also had another-- another group of people flying above, whom the Russians weren't aware of, didn't see.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
